        <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center mt-4 mb-4"><img src="~/images/learn/building user interface/screenshot_1.png" class="img-fluid" /></div>
        <p class="mt-3">After adjusting the dimensions of the global container, the application will dynamically adapt its height and width to match the screen size. Make the Height  & Width to (Parent.height/width) accordingly.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Grid Systems: Utilizing grid systems to structure the layout, allowing for consistent spacing and alignment across different screen sizes.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center mt-4 mb-4"><img src="~/images/learn/building user interface/screenshot_2.png" class="img-fluid" /></div>
        <p class="mt-3">From here, users can select multiple templates from the list, allowing them to utilize the same template across various screens. This ensures consistency throughout the app's design, preventing it from appearing disjointed or inconsistent.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Dynamic Sizing: Components such as images, text boxes, and buttons are set to adjust their size proportionally to the available screen space.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center mt-4 mb-4"><img src="~/images/learn/building user interface/screenshot_3.png" class="img-fluid" /></div>
